    <node id="ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code">
      <data key="d0">ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a regulatory framework influencing revisions to flange and fitting standards.&lt;SEP&gt;ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a technical standard specifying material requirements for bolting and pressure vessel components.&lt;SEP&gt;ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a technical standard referenced for material specifications and metallurgical requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a technical standard that includes qualified weld procedures and specifications for pipe fittings.&lt;SEP&gt;ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a regulatory framework providing material stress and strength data for pressure equipment design.&lt;SEP&gt;The ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code is a technical standard defining pressure–temperature ratings and material classifications for engineering applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c551c98db1e7353686af155387c310fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9866fd2e84ba4e57228a299a787a799b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30dae618425190cfb2b37b3fc339e4ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2db4306792ec2cf2ecdecd4354e069d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77ceed3fa636020b8c4e26e88b0bf466&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd686a0d0ac2ddced9bbfccb948905fd</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776334508</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
